commit.message: Use tox for testing and test more versions

Raise `KeyError` when the dependency is not found in the container (#2)

Previously the `provide` method returned `None` if the dependency was not found. This could
potentially delay code errors in case one made a typo in the dependency path.
Now when the `KeyError` is raised, application will fail instantly.
List the changes introduced by version 0.3.0.
Put back `__call__` as a shortcut for `provide`.
Import service and factory in example.
Use factory and service in example.
Add mock as a requirement for travis.
Add test for method to register a service.
Add test for method to register a factory.
Use alternative as an alternative name in test.
Use pass if return value is not tested.
Use mocks to test the decorators.
Remove cache argument from factory decorator.
Add missing return statements to decorators.
Always return false if the registered value is not an instance of FunctionCache.
Change the order of some tests.
Rename magic __call__ to an explicit method name.
Do not treat the default value as a provider if it's callable.
Improve test with alternative provider name.
Change the factory decorator to a function.
Remove some words from class description.

Add the ability to check whether a cacheable factory is cached. The function
  `cache_function` is removed in favor of the `FunctionCache` class.
Update example according to changes in terminology.
Rename test file to support test discovery.
Rename requirements file for Travis CI.
Update wrapper to look like service.
Drop support for Python 2.6 for now.
Fix typo, run-tests instead of run-test.

issue_comments.body: At the moment it's possible to pass a default return value in case a name is not registered. AFAIK this wouldn't be possible with the change you're suggesting. I guess the current funcionality of passing in a default return value is not that important IMHO. I'm willing to sacrifice the current behaviour in favor of this change. So, feel free to send a PR and I will merge. Thanks in advance!
Thanks for your PR, very appriciated!
